("sulfate_mod.f")          from "bravo_mod.f" for BRAVO Mexican emissions



Updates to Files in the Run Directory:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

globchem.dat		-- Now set the rxn HO2 --> 0.5 H2O2 (uptake of HO2
			   on aerosols to be inactive in the SMVGEAR mechanism.
			   Bastien Sauvage says there is better agreement in 
			   the tropics this way.
			-- From v7-04-05: added LISOPOH to get the amount of
			   ISOP that reacts with OH.

input.geos		-- Added "Use BRAVO Emissions?" line for logical
			   switch LBRAVO.  This turns BRAVO Mexican emissions
			   on/off.
